The festival of banderilles which concludes with the bulls racing at the fair of Pozoblanco has been suspended yesterday morning, after the horse keepers have established that the ring was unusable.
In this way, the organizing committee, in accordance with Fermín Bohórquez, Pablo Hermoso of Mendoza and Leonard Hernández, has decided to suspend the celebration of the bulls race.
Bad weather has hit the fair, because ultimately two festivals out of three could not take place.
Saturday the rain prevented the celebration of the second scheduled bulls race.
